  "texts": [
    "Without loss of generality, it is assumed that both the BS and user employ full digital beamforming, i.e., each antenna is connected to a dedicated radio frequency (RF) chain.",
    "At the transmitter, the digital baseband signal x is first processed by full digital beamforming and then converted to an analogue signal by a digital-to-analogue converter (DAC).",
    "Finally, the analogue signal is transmitted by the transmit antennas.",
    "At the receiver, the signal collected by the receive antennas is first converted to digital bits by an analogue-to-digital converter (ADC) and then processed by the receive beamforming to output the digital baseband signal y.",
    "Without loss of generality, we will examine the baseband signal processing in the following.The transmit signal at the BS can be formulated asx c = V x,(6)where x ∼ CN (0, I) ∈ C Nt×1 represents the communication symbols vector, and V ∈ C Nt×Nt denotes the transmit beamforming matrix.The received signal at the user can be written as where H ∈ C Nr×Nt denotes the channel matrix from the BS to the user, n ∼ CN (0, σ 2 n I) ∈ C Nr×1 represents the AWGN vector, and σ 2 n stands for the noise power."
  ]
